	(38,3,1,202,NULL,'2016-01-06 15:43:33',NULL,1,NULL,0),
	(23,3,1,200,'<h2>Bristol Hotel Rooms and Suites That Feel Like Home</h2>\n\n<p>Relax in contemporary rooms and suites in beautiful Bristol, Connecticut, designed with stylish d&eacute;cor in warm, inviting tones. Newly renovated in 2013 with a stylish, modern aesthetic, all of our spacious rooms and upgraded suites feature lifestyle essentials and travel-smart amenities that make you feel at home, but much better. With a new, contemporary design and sleek furniture, all of our 141 rooms surround you in comfort and convenience.</p>\n\n<h3>Designer Luxury For Modern Travelers</h3>\n\n<p>Enjoy a restful sleep in sumptuous king or queen beds and wake refreshed for the day ahead. Stay entertained with 42&quot; HDTVs with expanded channels and iHome docking stations, or catch up with the office with a work desk, wireless internet and two telephones with voicemail. When you need to relax, enjoy CITRON by Crabtree &amp; Evelyn toiletries and a dual cup Wolfgang Puck coffee maker. Upgrade to a suite for a touch of luxury and enjoy extra space to stretch out with separate sleeping and living areas.</p>\n\n<h3>Amenities &amp; Features You Love</h3>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>42&quot; HD Flat Screen HDTVs</li>\n	<li>iHome Docking Stations with Clock Radio</li>\n	<li>Coffee Makers By Keurig</li>\n	<li>Bathrobes (for Suites and Deluxe Rooms Only)</li>\n	<li>Bathroom TV (Presidential Suite Only)</li>\n	<li>Blackout Drapes</li>\n	<li>Chair and Ottoman</li>\n	<li>Complimentary High Speed &amp; Wireless Internet</li>\n	<li>Complimentary Newspaper</li>\n	<li>Citron By Crabtree &amp; Evelyn Toiletries</li>\n	<li>SAFLOK RFID Keys</li>\n	<li>Free Local Calls</li>\n	<li>Hair Dryer</li>\n	<li>Housekeeping</li>\n	<li>In-Room Safe (Accommodates Laptop)</li>\n	<li>Iron/Ironing Board</li>\n	<li>Microwave (On Request)</li>\n	<li>Wet Bar</li>\n	<li>Pay Movies</li>\n	<li>60 Cable TV Channels</li>\n	<li>Refrigerator</li>\n	<li>Slippers (for Suites and Deluxe Rooms Only)</li>\n	<li>Sofa Bed (for Suites Only)</li>\n	<li>Two Telephones W/ Voice Mail</li>\n	<li>Work Desk &amp; Ergonomic Chair</li>\n	<li>Wake Up Calls</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>King &amp; Queen Standard Room</h3>\n\n<p>The comfort of the Sweet Dreams by DoubleTree plush top king or 2 queen beds is the centerpiece of this custom-designed room. Lie back on the five jumbo down pillows or relax in the oversized chair with ottoman and flip through more than 60 HD channels on the 42&quot; HDTV. When you need to work, sit at the large desk with an ergonomic executive chair and connect with free high-speed internet. This signature room also features a refrigerator, Keurig coffee maker, iHome docking station, and a safe large enough for a laptop. Order up room service and kick back in style.</p>\n\n<h3>1 King Deluxe</h3>\n\n<p>Enjoy a peaceful night&#39;s sleep in Sweet Dreams by DoubleTree plush top king bed with five jumbo hypo-allergenic down pillows for sublime comfort. This deluxe designer room features all of our standard luxuries, including a Keurig coffee maker, iHome docking station, safe, and iron/ironing board. Relax in the comfortable chair with ottoman, flip through 60 channels on the 42&quot; LED TV, or tune out with the iHome docking. Stay productive with a large work desk, ergonomic chair and free WiFi. You will feel at home in our deluxe room, which also includes a plush bathrobe and slippers to relax with and upgraded bath amenities.</p>\n\n<h3>2 Queen Bed Suite</h3>\n\n<p>This designer two-room suite is an oasis of hospitality where you can work, relax, and entertain in modern comfort. Slip into a heavenly sleep in the separate bedroom, featuring two plush-top queen beds with five jumbo down pillows, triple sheeted down blanket and cozy coverlet. Sit back and lounge in the chic living room, with an overstuffed chair and ottoman, 42&quot; HDTV with over 60 channels, wet bar, and a pluh sofa bed that&#39;s perfect for families with kids. Our spacious suite features a guest bath with a glass enclosed shower. Get down to business at the large desk with an ergonomic chair, telephone with voicemail and complimentary high-speed and wireless internet.</p>\n\n<h3>King Bed Suite</h3>\n\n<p>Located in our Suite Tower, this beautiful one-bedroom suite gives you space and designer luxury you need for work and relaxation on the road. The bedroom features the Sweet Dreams by DoubleTree plush top king bed with five jumbo down pillows, a triple sheeted down blanket and cozy coverlet so you enjoy home-like comfort. Sit in the stylish living room, separated from your bedroom, catch a movie on the 42&quot;HDTV with over 60 channels and prepare a snack or drink at the wet bar. Our luxurious King Suite features a guest bath with a glass enclosed shower. When you need to finish a presentation, there&#39;s a large desk with an ergonomic chair, and complimentary high-speed internet access. Relax on the overstuffed chair with an ottoman and take advantage of in-room dining with farm-to-fork foods.</p>\n\n<h3>Presidential Suite</h3>\n\n<p>A luxurious sanctuary on the top floor of our Suite Tower, this spectacular 2,000 sq. ft. four-room suite is designed with artful d&eacute;cor and plenty of space to stretch out, relax, work, dine and entertain. The Presidential Suite features a private bedroom with a Sweet Dreams by DoubleTree plush top king bed with five jumbo hypo-allergenic down pillows. A triple sheeted down blanket and cozy coverlet gives you &quot;at home&quot; comfort. Lounge in the spacious living room, which is separated from your bedroom by a door, and enjoy the comfort of your den at home with a 64&quot; HDTV, a dining table for 8, a full kitchen, theatre area and a double sleeper sofa. This luxurious suite features 2 bathrooms for the guest to enjoy: a half bath, adjacent to the living room, and a full bath, adjacent to the sleeping room and complete with 2 TVs each housed in its own vanity. When the office calls, stay productive at the functional work space with an ergonomic chair and overstuffed chair with ottoman. Grab a snack from the mini bar or indulge in en-suite dining.</p>\n','2016-01-06 15:23:09','2016-01-06 15:23:09',1,1,0),
	(37,3,1,216,'<h2>Hotel Deals For Easy Getaways in Bristol, CT</h2>\n\n<p>From family vacations to golf adventures to romantic weekends, the DoubleTree by Hilton Bristol offers exciting hotel deals and specials for easy escapes to Bristol, Connecticut. Whether you are planning a last-minute getaway, a bed and breakfast retreat, or a business trip, you can count on our Manager&#39;s Special for a spectacular hotel experience and the best savings&nbsp;<br />\nin town.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Book Ahead Package</strong> - Save up to 20% on your family getaway when you book your summer break early. Come for a relaxing weekend, with a lazy breakfast until 11 a.m. and checkouts as late as 6 p.m. So plan a relaxing summer vacation ahead of the crowds and enjoy more for less. Don&#39;t forget that kids stay and eat free.</p>\n','2016-01-06 15:42:17','2016-01-06 15:42:17',1,1,0),
	(58,3,1,205,'<h2>Things To Do in Bristol, Connecticut</h2>\n\n<p>Named one of Money magazine&#39;s &quot;best place to live&quot; in America, Bristol is a beautiful suburb of Hartford with a rich history and classic New England charm. Home of ESPN headquarters, the city offers trendy shopping and dining, entertainment, beautiful parks and many fun things to do - from the New England Carousel Museum to exploring the forest trails at the Barnes Memorial Nature Center. They city also offers a myriad of exciting events and attractions, including Lake Compounce, the oldest continuously-operated amusement park in America, Imagine Nation Children&#39;s Museum, American Clock &amp; Watch Museum and the Bristol Mum Festival. The DoubleTree by Hilton Bristol is the perfect place for a family getaway or adventure.</p>\n\n<h3>Lake Compounce Family Theme Park</h3>\n\n<p>Dive into adventure at New England&#39;s exciting family theme and waterpark with thrilling rides, coasters, water slides, and shows. Ride Boulder Dash, the top wooden roller coaster in the world, and get wild at Crocodile Cove, Connecticut&#39;s largest waterpark.<br />\nVisit Website<br />\n<br />\n186 Enterprise Drive,&nbsp;Bristol,&nbsp;Connecticut&nbsp;06010<br />\n860-583-3300</p>\n\n<h3>New Britain Museum of American Art</h3>\n\n<p>Founded in 1903, the New Britain Museum of American Art is the first museum in the country dedicated to American art. Experience the impressive collection of Colonial portraits, Impressionist paintings and works by artists like Georgia O&#39;Keefe and Norman Rockwell.<br />\nVisit Website</p>\n\n<p>56 Lexington St,&nbsp;New Britain,&nbsp;Connecticut&nbsp;06052<br />\n860-229-0257</p>\n\n<h3>American Clock and Watch Museum</h3>\n\n<p>Located in the historic heart of American clockmaking, the American Clock &amp; Watch Museum highlights the rich history, science and art of timekeeping. The world&#39;s preeminent horological museum features American clocks mostly of the 19th and early 20th century.<br />\nVisit Website</p>\n\n<p>100 Maple St,&nbsp;Bristol,&nbsp;Connecticut&nbsp;06010<br />\n860-583-6070</p>\n\n<h3>Tunxis Plantation Golf Course</h3>\n\n<p>Tunxis Plantation GC features 45 holes of spectacular golf in the scenic landscape of Farmington Valley. Play the links-style, 18-hole Green Course, picturesque White Course and the original 9-hole Red Course with views of the Farmington River.<br />\nVisit Website</p>\n\n<p>87 Town Farm Road,&nbsp;Farmington,&nbsp;Connecticut&nbsp;06033<br />\n860-677-1367</p>\n\n<h3>Connecticut Wine Trail</h3>\n\n<p>Meander through the CT Wine Trail, one of the most exciting wine regions in the country, with 24 charming wineries and stunning New England scenery. Follow the blue trail signs and sip amazing wines at wineries such as Sunset Meadow Vineyards and Miranda Vineyard.<br />\nVisit Website</p>\n\n<p>195 Farmington Avenue,&nbsp;Farmington,&nbsp;Connecticut&nbsp;06032<br />\n860-677-5467</p>\n\n<h3>Connecticut Science Center</h3>\n\n<p>Overlooking the Connecticut River in Hartford, the attraction features interactive exhibits of science, art, nature and music in its multi-media galleries. Explore the galaxy and a black hole, learn about Connecticut&#39;s river ecosystem, and experience the feeling of sound.<br />\nVisit Website</p>\n\n<p>250 Columbus Blvd,&nbsp;Hartford,&nbsp;Connecticut&nbsp;06103<br />\n860-724-3623</p>\n\n<h3>Foxwoods Resort Casino</h3>\n\n<p>This casino is the most exciting gaming and entertainment destination in the Northeast. Foxwoods features six casinos, trendy dining, exclusive shopping, luxury spas, championship golf courses, live entertainment and outstanding concerts and shows.<br />\nVisit Website</p>\n\n<p>350 Trolley Line Blvd,&nbsp;Mashantucket,&nbsp;Connecticut&nbsp;06338<br />\n860-312-3000</p>\n\n<h3>Mohegan Sun Casino</h3>\n\n<p>One of the most amazing casino resorts in the country, Mohegan Sun boasts three world-class casinos, live entertainment, fine dining, shopping, a luxury spa, spectacular golf and the hottest concerts and sporting events, including the WNBA&#39;s Connecticut Sun.<br />\nVisit Website</p>\n\n<p>1 Mohegan Sun Blvd,&nbsp;Montville,&nbsp;Connecticut&nbsp;06382<br />\n888-226-7711</p>\n\n<h3>Rogers Orchards</h3>\n\n<p>A bicentennial farm and Connecticut landmark of eight generations of family fruit growing, Rogers Orchards sells seasonal fruits and vegetables, including vine-ripe tomatoes and sweet corn. Stock up on apples, cider, and pies as you discover the local farming heritage.<br />\nVisit Website</p>\n\n<p>336 Long Bottom Rd,&nbsp;Southington,&nbsp;Connecticut&nbsp;06489<br />\n860-229-4240</p>\n','2016-01-07 11:49:14','2016-01-07 11:49:14',1,1,0),
