	(42,3,1,203,'<h2>Meetings &amp; Events in Bristol, CT - Inspired Spaces Where Imagination Lives</h2>\n\n<p>Get connected, stay inspired and celebrate life&#39;s special moments at the DoubleTree by Hilton Bristol, where events come to life and imagination is infinite. Host an important business meeting, seminar, social event or a romantic wedding at our sophisticated event destination in Bristol - just 20 minutes from Hartford. Our state-of-the-art conference center features over 7,200 square feet of flexible meeting, event and banquet space that can accommodate up to 500 people. Whether you are planning a powerhouse conference, a gala affair or an intimate party of friends, we offer stylish spaces, impeccable service and farm-fresh cuisine that transform your event into a flawless happening!</p>\n\n<p><strong>Corporate Meetings &amp; Conferences</strong> - From board meetings and conferences to trade shows and team building events, DoubleTree by Hilton Bristol delivers a sophisticated and high-tech business experience. Renovated in 2013, our cutting-edge event facility features nine modern meeting rooms, pre-function space and ballrooms with the latest communications and audio/visual technology to enhance your presentations and productions. Our professional meeting planners will work with you to coordinate all the details - from catered breaks to leadership-building activities to group accommodations.&nbsp; We make business work seamlessly.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Exceptional Events Near Hartford</strong> - When it comes to creating a magical special event, our hotel is the place where people come together and celebrations shine.&nbsp; Our inviting, modern spaces are ideal for everything from birthday and anniversary parties to reunions to receptions to company banquets. Whatever you envision, our event planning specialists can select a breathtaking event venue, from our elegant ballrooms to our more intimate banquet salons. With 5,151 sq. ft. of space, The Oaks is a gorgeous backdrop for life&#39;s quintessential festivities.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Romantic Wedding Celebrations </strong>- Celebrate your wedding with friends and family in Bristol. Our hotel offers magnificent spaces and beautiful ballrooms with chic design, style d&eacute;cor, and elegant accents. White linens, glistening candles and colorful flowers create a romantic atmosphere where love and joy blossom. Enjoy a glamorous evening of sumptuous farm-to-table cuisine created by our talented chefs. Our wedding planning team offers personalized service to help you every step of your wedding journey - from catering to decorations to your guest list. We also offer exquisite venues for rehearsal dinners, bridal showers, and bachelor/bachelorette parties.</p>\n\n<h3>Meeting &amp; Event Services - Imagination Inspired By Experience</h3>\n\n<p>When it has to matter or make a statement, you can count on the DoubleTree by Hilton Bristol to host an event that leaves a dramatic impression. Our cutting-edge hotel and meeting destination offers a comprehensive range of services and amenities that ensure your meetings and special events are everything you imagined and more.&nbsp; Whether it&#39;s a gathering of friends or a powerhouse convention with moving parts, we offer the tools, resources and logistical support to ensure your event is a success.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Technology that Illuminates</strong> - The DoubleTree by Hilton Bristol offers a dynamic setting and well-equipped meeting spaces with advanced audio/visual, communications capability, wireless internet, and an all-access business center so that your presentations and performances deliver a sensory experience. We also offer hands-on technology support to assist you with sound, lighting and live entertainment productions.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Catering - Food That Creates The Mood</strong> - Food sets the mood and vibe of your event. At DoubleTree by Hilton Bristol, we offer creative catering and seasonal farm-to-fork cuisine that gives your meetings and events the flavor and spice you crave. From festive cocktail parties with light hors d&#39;oeuvres to healthy meeting breaks to sumptuous sit-down banquets, our talented chefs and catering team will create a custom menu of gastronomic goodies that will fuel minds and feed your soul. All of our cuisine is created from fresh, seasonal ingredients harvested from local farms and sourced from regional vendors so that every bite is an adventure.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Event Planning By People Who Care</strong> - Take a break from your to-do list and let us help with the details. We offer professional event planning services and dedicated meeting specialists that work with you to coordinate your entire event, whether you&#39;re reserving a conference room or designing a wedding reception. Our creative team and unlimited resources take the guesswork out of event planning &mdash; so you can focus on your next big idea or just enjoy the moment. Whether you are planning a business meeting or a festive party, we&#39;ll do whatever it takes to make sure it is an expression of your vision. Start planning your meeting with the confidence that we have your back.</p>\n\n<h3>Event Services &amp; Amenities - Make it Happen</h3>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Professional Event Catering</li>\n	<li>Ballrooms &amp; Banquet Facilities</li>\n	<li>Private Banquet Entrance</li>\n	<li>Professional Meeting and Event Planners</li>\n	<li>Meeting &amp; Conference Rooms</li>\n</ul>\n','2016-01-06 16:19:34','2016-01-06 16:19:34',1,1,0),
	(39,3,1,202,'<h2>Dining in Bristol, Connecticut</h2>\n\n<p>Food is comfort. So spoil yourself with a delicious dining experience without leaving our hotel. Indulge in fresh, seasonal cuisine and boutique wines at&nbsp;The Willows, or meet friends at&nbsp;TimeOut&nbsp;for modern gastro-pub fare and craft beer. Whether you crave field-to-table cuisine or a juicy burger while you watch the game, the Doubletree by Hilton Bristol features two wonderful restaurants with creative cuisine and distinctive character. Unwind with after-dinner drinks at the bar, or stay in and enjoy in-room dining.</p>\n\n<p><strong>The Willows</strong>&nbsp;- With its modern design and stylish aesthetic, this is a contemporary restaurant serving creative, new American cuisine, focusing on farm fresh ingredients. The innovative, seasonal menu features farm-to-fork creations and regional interpretations of steak, seafood and vegetable dishes artfully plated. The menu changes regularly to highlight fresh, local foods of the season. Enhance your dining experience with our extensive selection of boutique wines from around the globe.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Hours: Breakfast 6:00 am - 10:00 am &amp; Dinner 6:00 pm - 10:00 pm.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Time Out</strong> - This casual restaurant and sports bar with classic pub food and an upscale, modern twist. Take a break from your busy day and enjoy a menu of delicious lite fare with seasonal flare, appetizers, burgers, small plates, and salads prepared with local, fresh ingredients. Meet friends for a cocktail, a glass of domestic and international wine, and sip 12 craft beers from around country. With its warm, relaxed atmosphere,&nbsp;Time Out&nbsp;is an inviting spot to enjoy a light lunch, have drinks with friends, or relax and catch a game on the large-screen televisions.</p>\n\n<p>Hours: Monday - Sunday: 11:00 am - 11:00 pm<br />\n&nbsp;</p>\n','2016-01-06 15:44:53','2016-01-06 15:44:53',1,1,0),
	(61,3,1,206,'<h2>Bristol Hotel Reviews - Experience the Difference</h2>\n\n<p>With our distinctive, new look and contemporary design, the newly-remodeled DoubleTree by Bristol delivers passionate service and modern lifestyle amenities to vacation and business travelers from around the country. Discover our quintessential character, caring culture and unsurpassed hospitality by reading our latest hotel reviews. Imagine your next getaway to our upscale hotel in Bristol, CT, where you feel at home and happiness is more than a warm chocolate chip cookie.</p>\n\n<div class=\"TA_selfserveprop\" id=\"TA_selfserveprop950\">\n<ul class=\"TA_links udP8sL\" id=\"pD8Dwv\">\n	<li class=\"PZJTtoMcNU\" id=\"kTN5NWGVMZq\"><a href=\"http://www.tripadvisor.com/\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"TripAdvisor\" src=\"http://www.tripadvisor.com/img/cdsi/img2/branding/150_logo-11900-2.png\" /></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<script src=\"http://www.jscache.com/wejs?wtype=selfserveprop&amp;uniq=950&amp;locationId=487316&amp;lang=en_US&amp;rating=true&amp;nreviews=4&amp;writereviewlink=true&amp;popIdx=true&amp;iswide=true&amp;border=false&amp;display_version=2\"></script>\n\n<p><strong>&quot;Unbelievable Service, Outstanding Hotel!&quot;</strong><br />\n<br />\nAfter being on the road for a week and staying in 5 different hotels, I arrived to this wonderful place and have been amazed since I checked in! Staff is beyond wonderful, room is immaculate, hotel grounds are beautiful and I can honestly say, this is the nicest place I have stayed in with a $100-300 price range. This hotel is so overwhelmingly wonderful, I had to write a review immediately- less than an hour after I checked in! 15 minutes or so after arriving at my room, the front desk called to make sure the room was acceptable and ask if there is anything I need. Now THAT hasn&#39;t happened at any other hotel I have stayed at in a long time. The staff here go out of their way to treat guests like royalty! So happy I decided to stay here! Thanks, Doubletree- I haven&#39;t even left yet but I will guarantee I&#39;ll be back!! &nbsp;Stayed May 2015, traveled on business<br />\n<br />\n<strong>&quot;Clean &amp; Modern Doubletree in Bristol&quot;</strong><br />\n<br />\nOur family of 5 had a great stay in the Doubletree hotel in Bristol, CT. We had an early event nearby which prompted our choice to stay there. The queen suite was so comfortable and spacious, we wish all hotels we stay in had this arrangement. The kids had a great time in the pool. The staff were very friendly and service was wonderful. We highly recommend this hotel.- by Susan B (New Canaan, CT, United States) on 3/31/14. Stay date: Mar 2014<br />\n<br />\n<strong>&quot;ESPN&quot;</strong><br />\n<br />\nNear the corporate headquarters of ESPN this hotel was conveniently located. The staff was very helpful and friendly. Cant beat the warm cookie at check in! room was spacious and the work out area was&nbsp;very nice. enjoyable breakfast- by Jill B (buffalo, United States) on 3/31/14. Stay date: Mar 2014<br />\n<br />\n<strong>&quot;A must stay!&quot;</strong><br />\n<br />\nFrom the time we walked in the front door, we were impressed. From the friendly greeting (with a delicious warm chocolate chip cookie, and if you have ever had one of these you know what I am talking about) to the spacious room, my experience at the hotel far exceeded my expectations. The sports bar was right on the money. There were several TVs&nbsp;with many games to choose from. The food was good and reasonably priced. The service was also very good. This place has a fitness center and a heated pool, although we did not get to experience either due to time restrictions on my part. The room was very nice and modern with 2 queen beds and HD TV . It also has a Keurig coffee maker which was great for that immediate morning cup. I highly recommend this hotel and it will be my choice the next time im staying in Bristol.- by Mike P (North Providence, Rhode Island) on 3/30/14. Stay date: Mar 2014<br />\n<br />\n<strong>&quot;repeatedly blown away at the customer service.&quot;</strong><br />\n<br />\nJust a brief note to tell you about my experience and the attitudes at the Bristol Doubletree Hotel. I am diamond at Hilton and Gold at Marriott, so needless to say I travel frequently. I am just finishing up my third stay here and I am repeatedly blown away at the customer service. Here are a few examples.<br />\n<br />\nEvelyis - a breathe of sunshine. She has an attitude of &quot;what else can I do,&nbsp; I love helping you.&quot;&nbsp; She gets it before I know I want it.<br />\n<br />\nRestaurant - The first time I was here they had a duck special. The second time I was here I asked if it was one of the specials. It wasn&#39;t but the made if for me anyway.&nbsp; It was delicious.<br />\n<br />\nLast time I was here&nbsp; I had left my blazer in the room. When I arrived&nbsp; yesterday my blazer was dry cleaned,&nbsp; pressed and waiting for me in my room.&nbsp; Now this is a wow!&nbsp;&nbsp; I asked who was in charge of doing this.&nbsp; It was Miguel.<br />\n<br />\nI have never been to a hotel where EVERYONE goes above and beyond.&nbsp; This attitude and work ethic obviously comes from the top. Kudos, you are doing an amazing job.<br />\n<br />\nSincerely,<br />\nAnonymous</p>\n','2016-01-07 14:55:27','2016-01-07 14:55:27',1,1,0),
