	(65,3,1,208,'<h3 style=\"font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; line-height: 22px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\">Getting Here Is Easy</h3>\n\n<p style=\"font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 16px; line-height: 22px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>From Hartford</strong>&nbsp;-Take I-84 West,&nbsp;Take Exit 33 onto Route 72 West towards Bristol, at end of expressway turn left onto Route 229/Middle Street. Go about 1 mile and the hotel is on the right.</p>\n\n<p style=\"font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 16px; line-height: 22px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>From New York City / Danbury</strong>&nbsp;- Take I-84 East, Take Exit 31, Left off ramp onto Route 229/West Street. After about 3 miles, the hotel will be on the left.</p>\n\n<p style=\"font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 16px; line-height: 22px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>From Bradley International Airport</strong>&nbsp;- Take I-91 South, to I-84 West, Take Exit 33 onto Route 72 West towards Bristol, at end of expressway turn left onto Route 229/Middle Street. Go about 1 mile and the hotel is on the right.</p>\n\n<h3>Hotel in Bristol, Connecticut</h3>\n\n<p>Located in a charming city, midway between New York City and Boston, The DoubleTree by Hilton Hotel Bristol boasts an ideal address for business and leisure travelers. Our convenient hotel is one mile from ESPN Headquarters at the ESPN Plaza and just minutes from trendy shopping, dining, and entertainment. Our hotel also offers easy access to local businesses and corporations, downtown Hartford and Bradley International Airport.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Exciting Family Adventures</strong> - The DoubleTree by Hilton Hotel Bristol is close to many exciting activities, historic landmarks and attractions. Enjoy a family day trip to Lake Compounce Amusement Park and tour the New England Carousel Museum and Imagine Nation Children&#39;s Museum. Experience the beautiful vineyards and towns along the Connecticut Wine Trail or play on the majestic slopes of the Mt. Southington Ski Area. For outdoor action, explore the Barnes Nature Center and Adventure Balloon Rides.</p>\n\n<h3>Bristol Area Attractions</h3>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Lake Compounce&nbsp;- 1 mile</li>\n	<li>Carousel Museum of New England - 1 mile</li>\n	<li>ESPN Headquarters&nbsp;- 1 mile</li>\n	<li>American Clock and Watch Museum&nbsp;- 1 mile</li>\n	<li>Connecticut Wine Trail&nbsp;- 12.8 miles</li>\n	<li>The Barnes Nature Center&nbsp;- 3 miles</li>\n	<li>Imagine Nation Museum&nbsp;- 3 miles</li>\n	<li>Giamatti Little League Center&nbsp;- 3.5 miles</li>\n	<li>Thomaston Opera House - 7.3 miles</li>\n	<li>Mt. Southington Ski Area&nbsp;- 9.2 miles</li>\n	<li>Repertory Theater of New Britain&nbsp;- 9.3 miles</li>\n	<li>Adventure Balloon Rides&nbsp;- 9.5 miles</li>\n	<li>New Britain Museum of American Art&nbsp;- 10 miles</li>\n	<li>Litchfield Hills&nbsp;- 16.3 miles</li>\n	<li>Warner Theater Torrington&nbsp;- 18 miles</li>\n	<li>CT Science Center&nbsp;- 19 miles</li>\n	<li>Connecticut Convention Center&nbsp;- 20 miles</li>\n	<li>Downtown Hartford&nbsp;- 20 miles</li>\n	<li>Lyman Orchards&nbsp;- 23 miles</li>\n	<li>Lyman Orchards Golf Course&nbsp;- 23 miles</li>\n	<li>Mohegan Sun Casino&nbsp;- 55 miles</li>\n	<li>Foxwoods Casino&nbsp;- 60 miles</li>\n	<li>Bradley International Airport - 35 miles</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\n','2016-01-07 15:25:29','2016-01-07 15:25:29',1,1,0),
