	(96,3,1,205,'<h2>Things To Do in Bristol, Connecticut</h2>\n\n<p>Named one of Money magazine&#39;s &quot;best places to live&quot; in America, Bristol is a beautiful suburb of Hartford with a rich history and classic New England charm. Home of ESPN headquarters, the city offers trendy shopping and dining, entertainment, beautiful parks and many fun things to do - from the New England Carousel Museum to exploring the forest trails at the Barnes Memorial Nature Center. The city also offers a myriad of exciting events and attractions, including Lake Compounce, the oldest continuously-operated amusement park in America, Imagine Nation Children&#39;s Museum, American Clock &amp; Watch Museum and the Bristol Mum Festival. The DoubleTree by Hilton Bristol is the perfect place for a family getaway or adventure.</p>\n\n<h3>Lake Compounce Family Theme Park</h3>\n\n<p>Dive into adventure at New England&#39;s exciting family theme and waterpark with thrilling rides, coasters, water slides and shows. Ride Boulder Dash, the top wooden roller coaster in the world, and get wild at Crocodile Cove, Connecticut&#39;s largest waterpark.<br />\n<a href=\"http://www.lakecompounce.com/\">Visit Website</a><br />\n<br />\n186 Enterprise Drive,&nbsp;Bristol,&nbsp;Connecticut&nbsp;06010<br />\n860-583-3300</p>\n\n<h3>New Britain Museum of American Art</h3>\n\n<p>Founded in 1903, the New Britain Museum of American Art is the first museum in the country dedicated to American art. Experience the impressive collection of Colonial portraits, Impressionist paintings and works by artists like Georgia O&#39;Keefe and Norman Rockwell.<br />\n<a href=\"http://www.nbmaa.org/\">Visit Website</a></p>\n\n<p>56 Lexington St,&nbsp;New Britain,&nbsp;Connecticut&nbsp;06052<br />\n860-229-0257</p>\n\n<h3>American Clock and Watch Museum</h3>\n\n<p>Located in the historic heart of American clockmaking, the American Clock &amp; Watch Museum highlights the rich history, science and art of timekeeping. The world&#39;s preeminent horological museum features American clocks mostly of the 19th and early 20th century.<br />\n<a href=\"http://www.clockandwatchmuseum.org/\">Visit Website</a></p>\n\n<p>100 Maple St,&nbsp;Bristol,&nbsp;Connecticut&nbsp;06010<br />\n860-583-6070</p>\n\n<h3>Tunxis Plantation Golf Course</h3>\n\n<p>Tunxis Plantation GC features 45 holes of spectacular golf in the scenic landscape of Farmington Valley. Play the links, 18-hole Green Course, picturesque White Course and the original 9-hole Red Course with views of the Farmington River.<br />\n<a href=\"http://www.tunxisgolf.com/\">Visit Website</a></p>\n\n<p>87 Town Farm Road,&nbsp;Farmington,&nbsp;Connecticut&nbsp;06033<br />\n860-677-1367</p>\n\n<h3>Connecticut Wine Trail</h3>\n\n<p>Meander through the CT Wine Trail, one of the most exciting wine regions in the country, with 24 charming wineries and stunning New England scenery. Follow the blue trail signs and sip amazing wines at wineries such as Sunset Meadow Vineyards and Miranda Vineyard.<br />\n<a href=\"http://www.ctwine.com/\">Visit Website</a></p>\n\n<p>195 Farmington Avenue,&nbsp;Farmington,&nbsp;Connecticut&nbsp;06032<br />\n860-677-5467</p>\n\n<h3>Connecticut Science Center</h3>\n\n<p>Overlooking the Connecticut River in Hartford, this attraction features interactive exhibits of science, art, nature and music in its multi-media galleries. Explore the galaxy and a black hole, learn about Connecticut&#39;s river ecosystem and experience the feeling of sound.<br />\n<a href=\"http://www.ctsciencecenter.org/\">Visit Website</a></p>\n\n<p>250 Columbus Blvd,&nbsp;Hartford,&nbsp;Connecticut&nbsp;06103<br />\n860-724-3623</p>\n\n<h3>Foxwoods Resort Casino</h3>\n\n<p>This casino is the most exciting gaming and entertainment destination in the Northeast. Foxwoods features six casinos, trendy dining, exclusive shopping, luxury spas, championship golf courses, live entertainment and outstanding concerts and shows.<br />\n<a href=\"http://www.foxwoods.com/\">Visit Website</a></p>\n\n<p>350 Trolley Line Blvd,&nbsp;Mashantucket,&nbsp;Connecticut&nbsp;06338<br />\n860-312-3000</p>\n\n<h3>Mohegan Sun Casino</h3>\n\n<p>One of the most amazing casino resorts in the country, Mohegan Sun boasts three world-class casinos, live entertainment, fine dining, shopping, a luxury spa, spectacular golf and the hottest concerts and sporting events, including the WNBA&#39;s Connecticut Sun.<br />\n<a href=\"http://www.mohegansun.com/\">Visit Website</a></p>\n\n<p>1 Mohegan Sun Blvd,&nbsp;Montville,&nbsp;Connecticut&nbsp;06382<br />\n888-226-7711</p>\n\n<h3>Rogers Orchards</h3>\n\n<p>A bicentennial farm and Connecticut landmark of eight generations of family fruit growing, Rogers Orchards sells seasonal fruits and vegetables, including vine-ripe tomatoes and sweet corn. Stock up on apples, cider, and pies as you discover the local farming heritage.<br />\n<a href=\"http://www.rogersorchards.com/\">Visit Website</a></p>\n\n<p>336 Long Bottom Rd,&nbsp;Southington,&nbsp;Connecticut&nbsp;06489<br />\n860-229-4240</p>\n','2016-02-05 11:29:52','2016-02-05 11:29:52',15,15,0),
	(97,3,1,206,'<h2>Bristol Hotel Reviews - Experience the Difference</h2>\n\n<p>With our distinctive, new look and contemporary design, the newly-remodeled DoubleTree by Bristol delivers passionate service and modern lifestyle amenities to vacation and business travelers from around the country. Discover our quintessential character, caring culture and unsurpassed hospitality by reading our latest hotel reviews. Imagine your next getaway to our upscale hotel in Bristol, CT, where you feel at home and happiness is more than a warm chocolate chip cookie.</p>\n\n<div class=\"TA_selfserveprop\" id=\"TA_selfserveprop950\">\n<p class=\"PZJTtoMcNU\"><a href=\"http://www.tripadvisor.com/\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"TripAdvisor\" src=\"http://www.tripadvisor.com/img/cdsi/img2/branding/150_logo-11900-2.png\" /></a></p>\n</div>\n<script src=\"http://www.jscache.com/wejs?wtype=selfserveprop&uniq=950&locationId=487316&lang=en_US&rating=true&nreviews=4&writereviewlink=true&popIdx=true&iswide=true&border=false&display_version=2\"></script>\n\n<p><strong>&quot;Unbelievable Service, Outstanding Hotel!&quot;</strong><br />\n<br />\nAfter being on the road for a week and staying in 5 different hotels, I arrived to this wonderful place and have been amazed since I checked in! Staff is beyond wonderful, room is immaculate, hotel grounds are beautiful and I can honestly say, this is the nicest place I have stayed in with a $100-300 price range. This hotel is so overwhelmingly wonderful, I had to write a review immediately- less than an hour after I checked in! 15 minutes or so after arriving at my room, the front desk called to make sure the room was acceptable and ask if there is anything I need. Now THAT hasn&#39;t happened at any other hotel I have stayed at in a long time. The staff here go out of their way to treat guests like royalty! So happy I decided to stay here! Thanks, Doubletree- I haven&#39;t even left yet but I will guarantee I&#39;ll be back!! &nbsp;Stayed May 2015, traveled on business<br />\n<br />\n<strong>&quot;Clean &amp; Modern Doubletree in Bristol&quot;</strong><br />\n<br />\nOur family of 5 had a great stay in the Doubletree hotel in Bristol, CT. We had an early event nearby which prompted our choice to stay there. The queen suite was so comfortable and spacious, we wish all hotels we stay in had this arrangement. The kids had a great time in the pool. The staff were very friendly and service was wonderful. We highly recommend this hotel.- by Susan B (New Canaan, CT) on 3/31/14. Stay date: Mar 2014<br />\n<br />\n<strong>&quot;ESPN&quot;</strong><br />\n<br />\nNear the corporate headquarters of ESPN this hotel was conveniently located. The staff was very helpful and friendly. Cant beat the warm cookie at check in! Room was spacious and the work out area was&nbsp;very nice. enjoyable breakfast- by Jill B (Buffalo, NY) on 3/31/14. Stay date: Mar 2014<br />\n<br />\n<strong>&quot;A must stay!&quot;</strong><br />\n<br />\nFrom the time we walked in the front door, we were impressed. From the friendly greeting (with a delicious warm chocolate chip cookie, and if you have ever had one of these you know what I am talking about) to the spacious room, my experience at the hotel far exceeded my expectations. The sports bar was right on the money. There were several TVs&nbsp;with many games to choose from. The food was good and reasonably priced. The service was also very good. This place has a fitness center and a heated pool, although we did not get to experience either due to time restrictions on my part. The room was very nice and modern with 2 queen beds and HD TV . It also has a Keurig coffee maker which was great for that immediate morning cup. I highly recommend this hotel and it will be my choice the next time im staying in Bristol.- by Mike P (North Providence, RI) on 3/30/14. Stay date: Mar 2014<br />\n<br />\n<strong>&quot;repeatedly blown away at the customer service.&quot;</strong><br />\n<br />\nJust a brief note to tell you about my experience and the attitudes at the Bristol Doubletree Hotel. I am diamond at Hilton and Gold at Marriott, so needless to say I travel frequently. I am just finishing up my third stay here and I am repeatedly blown away at the customer service. Here are a few examples.<br />\n<br />\nEvelyis - a breathe of sunshine. She has an attitude of &quot;what else can I do,&nbsp; I love helping you.&quot; She gets it before I know I want it.<br />\n<br />\nRestaurant - The first time I was here they had a duck special. The second time I was here I asked if it was one of the specials. It wasn&#39;t but the made if for me anyway. It was delicious.<br />\n<br />\nLast time I was here I had left my blazer in the room. When I arrived&nbsp; yesterday my blazer was dry cleaned,&nbsp; pressed and waiting for me in my room.&nbsp; Now this is a wow! I asked who was in charge of doing this. It was Miguel.<br />\n<br />\nI have never been to a hotel where EVERYONE goes above and beyond.&nbsp; This attitude and work ethic obviously comes from the top. Kudos, you are doing an amazing job.<br />\n<br />\nSincerely,<br />\nAnonymous</p>\n','2016-02-05 11:36:11','2016-02-05 11:36:11',15,15,0),
	(98,3,1,207,'<p style=\"font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 16px; line-height: 22px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong style=\"font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-size: 16px; line-height: 22px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\">Warm Hospitality with Contemporary Design </strong></p>\n\n<p style=\"font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 16px; line-height: 22px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\">Rated #1 in guest satisfaction among all DoubleTree Hotels in America! With it&#39;s distinctive style, contemporary design and newly-renovated spaces, The DoubleTree by Hilton Hotel Bristol is a high-end boutique hotel with a unique mix of New England character and high-tech capability. From the moment you walk into our inviting hotel, you are warmly welcomed with a smile and our delicious fresh-baked cookies. Surrounded by the charm of the city, our newly-renovated hotel gives you a sense of home in beautiful Central Connecticut.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p style=\"font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 16px; line-height: 22px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</p>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n','2016-02-05 11:43:26','2016-02-05 11:43:26',15,15,0),
	(99,3,1,208,'<h3 style=\"font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; line-height: 22px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\">Getting Here Is Easy</h3>\n\n<p style=\"font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 16px; line-height: 22px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>From Hartford</strong>&nbsp;-Take I-84 West,&nbsp;Take Exit 33 onto Route 72 West towards Bristol, at end of expressway turn left onto Route 229/Middle Street. Go about 1 mile and the hotel is on the right.</p>\n\n<p style=\"font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 16px; line-height: 22px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>From New York City / Danbury</strong>&nbsp;- Take I-84 East, Take Exit 31, Left off ramp onto Route 229/West Street. After about 3 miles, the hotel will be on the left.</p>\n\n<p style=\"font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 16px; line-height: 22px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>From Bradley International Airport</strong>&nbsp;- Take I-91 South, to I-84 West, Take Exit 33 onto Route 72 West towards Bristol, at end of expressway turn left onto Route 229/Middle Street. Go about 1 mile and the hotel is on the right.</p>\n\n<h3>Hotel in Bristol, Connecticut</h3>\n\n<p>Located in a charming city, midway between New York City and Boston, The DoubleTree by Hilton Hotel Bristol boasts an ideal address for business and leisure travelers. Our convenient hotel is one mile from ESPN Headquarters at the ESPN Plaza and just minutes from trendy shopping, dining and entertainment. Our hotel also offers easy access to local businesses and corporations, downtown Hartford and Bradley International Airport.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Exciting Family Adventures</strong> - The DoubleTree by Hilton Hotel Bristol is close to many exciting activities, historic landmarks and attractions. Enjoy a family day trip to Lake Compounce Amusement Park and tour the New England Carousel Museum and Imagine Nation Children&#39;s Museum. Experience the beautiful vineyards and towns along the Connecticut Wine Trail or play on the majestic slopes of the Mt. Southington Ski Area. For outdoor action, explore the Barnes Nature Center and Adventure Balloon Rides.</p>\n\n<h3>Bristol Area Attractions</h3>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Lake Compounce&nbsp;- 1 mile</li>\n	<li>Carousel Museum of New England - 1 mile</li>\n	<li>ESPN Headquarters&nbsp;- 1 mile</li>\n	<li>American Clock and Watch Museum&nbsp;- 1 mile</li>\n	<li>Connecticut Wine Trail&nbsp;- 12.8 miles</li>\n	<li>The Barnes Nature Center&nbsp;- 3 miles</li>\n	<li>Imagine Nation Museum&nbsp;- 3 miles</li>\n	<li>Giamatti Little League Center&nbsp;- 3.5 miles</li>\n	<li>Thomaston Opera House - 7.3 miles</li>\n	<li>Mt. Southington Ski Area&nbsp;- 9.2 miles</li>\n	<li>Repertory Theater of New Britain&nbsp;- 9.3 miles</li>\n	<li>Adventure Balloon Rides&nbsp;- 9.5 miles</li>\n	<li>New Britain Museum of American Art&nbsp;- 10 miles</li>\n	<li>Litchfield Hills&nbsp;- 16.3 miles</li>\n	<li>Warner Theater Torrington&nbsp;- 18 miles</li>\n	<li>CT Science Center&nbsp;- 19 miles</li>\n	<li>Connecticut Convention Center&nbsp;- 20 miles</li>\n	<li>Downtown Hartford&nbsp;- 20 miles</li>\n	<li>Lyman Orchards&nbsp;- 23 miles</li>\n	<li>Lyman Orchards Golf Course&nbsp;- 23 miles</li>\n	<li>Mohegan Sun Casino&nbsp;- 55 miles</li>\n	<li>Foxwoods Casino&nbsp;- 60 miles</li>\n	<li>Bradley International Airport - 35 miles</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\n','2016-02-05 11:46:58','2016-02-05 11:46:58',15,15,0),
	(100,3,1,209,'<h2>Bristol CT Hotel Reservations - Travel Made Easy</h2>\n\n<p>When you need to make hotel reservations in Bristol, the DoubleTree by Hilton makes business and vacation travel easy and affordable. Our courteous reservations team is always on hand to help you book your stay - whether it&#39;s a family getaway, an essential business meeting or last-minute weekend escape. With our contemporary design, engaging spaces and passionate service, our hotel surrounds you in modern comfort and capability - from the heated atrium pool and the high-tech business center to our trendy dining spots.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Inviting Spaces, Caring People</strong> - Please contact us to make your hotel reservations, plan a special event or take advantage of our unique hotel packages. We look forward to welcoming you to Bristol with our warm smiles and famous freshly-baked cookies.</p>\n','2016-02-05 11:48:17','2016-02-05 11:48:17',15,15,0),
	(101,3,1,202,'<h2>Dining in Bristol, Connecticut</h2>\n\n<p>Food is comfort. So spoil yourself with a delicious dining experience without leaving our hotel. Indulge in fresh, seasonal cuisine and boutique wines at&nbsp;The Willows, or meet friends at&nbsp;TimeOut&nbsp;for modern gastro-pub fare and craft beer. Whether you crave farm-to-table cuisine or a juicy burger while you watch the game, the Doubletree by Hilton Bristol features two wonderful restaurants with creative cuisine and distinctive character. Unwind with after-dinner drinks at the bar, or stay in and enjoy in-room dining.</p>\n\n<p><strong>The Willows</strong>&nbsp;- With its modern design and stylish aesthetic, this is a contemporary restaurant serving creative, new American cuisine, focusing on farm fresh ingredients. The innovative, seasonal menu features farm-to-fork creations and regional interpretations of steak, seafood and vegetable dishes artfully plated. The menu changes regularly to highlight fresh, local foods of the season. Enhance your dining experience with our extensive selection of boutique wines from around the globe.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Hours: Breakfast 6:00 am - 10:00 am &amp; Dinner 6:00 pm - 10:00 pm.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Time Out</strong> - This casual restaurant and sports bar with classic pub food and an upscale, modern twist. Take a break from your busy day and enjoy a menu of delicious lite fare with seasonal flare, appetizers, burgers, small plates, and salads prepared with local, fresh ingredients. Meet friends for a cocktail, a glass of domestic and international wine, and sip 12 craft beers from around country. With its warm, relaxed atmosphere,&nbsp;Time Out&nbsp;is an inviting spot to enjoy a light lunch, have drinks with friends, or relax and catch a game on the large-screen televisions.</p>\n\n<p>Hours: Monday - Sunday: 11:00 am - 11:00 pm<br />\n&nbsp;</p>\n','2016-02-05 12:19:54','2016-02-05 12:19:54',15,15,0),
	(102,3,1,200,'<h2><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Designer Luxury in Bristol For Modern Travelers</span></h2>\n\n<p>All of our rooms and suites are contemporary and designed with stylish <span style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: 22px;\">d&eacute;cor in warm, inviting tones. In beautiful Bristol, Connecticut and newly renovated in 2013, all of our 141 rooms surround you in comfort and convenience.</span>&nbsp;Enjoy a restful sleep in luxurious king or queen beds and wake refreshed for the day ahead. Stay entertained with 42&quot; HDTVs with expanded channels and iHome docking stations, or catch up with the office with a work desk, wireless internet and two telephones with voicemail. When you need to relax, enjoy CITRON by Crabtree &amp; Evelyn toiletries and a dual cup Wolfgang Puck coffee maker. Upgrade to a suite for a touch of luxury and enjoy extra space to stretch out with separate sleeping and living areas.</p>\n\n<p><strong style=\"font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-size: 16px; line-height: 22px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\">Check-In Time</strong><span style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: 22px;\">&nbsp;- 3:00 pm</span><br />\n<strong style=\"font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-size: 16px; line-height: 22px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\">Check-Out Time</strong><span style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: 22px;\">&nbsp;- 12:00 pm</span></p>\n\n<p>Learn more about our diverse selection of rooms and suites below:</p>\n\n<h3>King &amp; Queen Standard Room</h3>\n\n<p>The comfort of the Sweet Dreams by DoubleTree plush top king or 2 queen beds is the centerpiece of this custom-designed room. Lie back on the five jumbo down pillows or relax in the oversized chair with ottoman and flip through more than 60 HD channels on the 42&quot; HDTV. When you need to work, sit at the large desk with an ergonomic executive chair and connect with free high-speed internet. This signature room also features a refrigerator, Keurig coffee maker, iHome docking station, and a safe large enough for a laptop. Order up room service and kick back in style.</p>\n\n<h3>1 King Deluxe</h3>\n\n<p>Enjoy a peaceful night&#39;s sleep in Sweet Dreams by DoubleTree plush top king bed with five jumbo hypo-allergenic down pillows for sublime comfort. This deluxe designer room features all of our standard luxuries, including a Keurig coffee maker, iHome docking station, safe, and iron/ironing board. Relax in the comfortable chair with ottoman, flip through 60 channels on the 42&quot; LED TV, or tune out with the iHome docking. Stay productive with a large work desk, ergonomic chair and free WiFi. You will feel at home in our deluxe room, which also includes a plush bathrobe and slippers to relax with and upgraded bath amenities.</p>\n\n<h3>2 Queen Bed Suite</h3>\n\n<p>This designer two-room suite is an oasis of hospitality where you can work, relax, and entertain in modern comfort. Slip into a heavenly sleep in the separate bedroom, featuring two plush-top queen beds with five jumbo down pillows, triple sheeted down blanket and cozy coverlet. Sit back and lounge in the chic living room, with an overstuffed chair and ottoman, 42&quot; HDTV with over 60 channels, wet bar, and a pluh sofa bed that&#39;s perfect for families with kids. Our spacious suite features a guest bath with a glass enclosed shower. Get down to business at the large desk with an ergonomic chair, telephone with voicemail and complimentary high-speed and wireless internet.</p>\n\n<h3>King Bed Suite</h3>\n\n<p>Located in our &nbsp;Tower, this beautiful one-bedroom suite gives you space and designer luxury you need for work and relaxation on the road. The bedroom features the Sweet Dreams by DoubleTree plush top king bed with five jumbo down pillows, a triple sheeted down blanket and cozy coverlet so you enjoy home-like comfort. Sit in the stylish living room, separated from your bedroom, catch a movie on the 42&quot;HDTV with over 60 channels and prepare a snack or drink at the wet bar. Our luxurious King Suite features a guest bath with a glass enclosed shower. When you need to finish a presentation, there&#39;s a large desk with an ergonomic chair, and complimentary high-speed internet access. Relax on the overstuffed chair with an ottoman and take advantage of in-room dining with farm-to-fork foods.</p>\n\n<h3>Presidential Suite</h3>\n\n<p>A luxurious sanctuary on the top floor of our Suite Tower, this spectacular 2,000 sq. ft. four-room suite is designed with artful d&eacute;cor and plenty of space to stretch out, relax, work, dine and entertain. The Presidential Suite features a private bedroom with a Sweet Dreams by DoubleTree plush top king bed with five jumbo hypo-allergenic down pillows. A triple sheeted down blanket and cozy coverlet gives you &quot;at home&quot; comfort. Lounge in the spacious living room, which is separated from your bedroom by a door, and enjoy the comfort of your den at home with a 64&quot; HDTV, a dining table for 8, a full kitchen, theatre area and a double sleeper sofa. This luxurious suite features 2 bathrooms for the guest to enjoy: a half bath, adjacent to the living room, and a full bath, adjacent to the sleeping room and complete with 2 TVs each housed in its own vanity. When the office calls, stay productive at the functional work space with an ergonomic chair and overstuffed chair with ottoman. Grab a snack from the mini bar or indulge in en-suite dining.</p>\n','2016-02-18 11:20:13','2016-02-18 11:20:13',1,1,0),
