ustomer Service.&quot;</strong><br />\n<br />\nJust a brief note to tell you about my experience and the attitudes at the Bristol Doubletree Hotel. I am diamond at Hilton and Gold at Marriott, so needless to say I travel frequently. I am just finishing up my third stay here and I am repeatedly blown away at the customer service. Here are a few examples.<br />\n<br />\nEvelyis - a breathe of sunshine. She has an attitude of &quot;what else can I do, I love helping you.&quot; She gets it before I know I want it.<br />\n<br />\nRestaurant - The first time I was here they had a duck special. The second time I was here I asked if it was one of the specials. It wasn&#39;t but they made if for me anyway. It was delicious.<br />\n<br />\nLast time I was here I had left my blazer in the room. When I arrived yesterday my blazer was dry cleaned, pressed and waiting for me in my room. Now, this is a wow! I asked who was in charge of doing this. It was Miguel.<br />\n<br />\nI have never been to a hotel where EVERYONE goes above and beyond. This attitude and work ethic obviously comes from the top. Kudos, you are doing an amazing job.<br />\n<br />\nSincerely,<br />\nAnonymous</p>\n','2016-02-24 16:28:19','2016-02-24 16:28:20',18,18,0),
	(167,3,1,207,'<p style=\"font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 16px; line-height: 22px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong style=\"font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-size: 16px; line-height: 22px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\">Warm Hospitality with Contemporary Design </strong></p>\n\n<p style=\"font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 16px; line-height: 22px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\">Rated #1 in guest satisfaction among all DoubleTree Hotels in America! With its distinctive style, contemporary design and newly-renovated spaces, The DoubleTree by Hilton Hotel Bristol is a high-end boutique hotel with a unique mix of New England character and high-tech capability. From the moment you walk into our inviting hotel, you are warmly welcomed with a smile and our delicious fresh-baked cookies. Surrounded by the charm of the city, our newly-renovated hotel gives you a sense of home in beautiful Central Connecticut.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p style=\"font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 16px; line-height: 22px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</p>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n','2016-02-24 16:30:43','2016-02-24 16:30:44',18,18,0),
	(168,3,1,208,'<h3 style=\"font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; line-height: 22px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\">Getting Here Is Easy</h3>\n\n<p style=\"font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 16px; line-height: 22px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>From Hartford</strong>&nbsp;-Take I-84 West, take Exit 33 onto Route 72 West toward Bristol. At end of expressway turn left onto Route 229/Middle Street. Go about 1 mile and the hotel is on the right.</p>\n\n<p style=\"font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 16px; line-height: 22px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>From New York City / Danbury</strong>&nbsp;- Take I-84 East, take Exit 31, left off ramp onto Route 229/West Street. After about 3 miles, the hotel will be on the left.</p>\n\n<p style=\"font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 16px; line-height: 22px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>From Bradley International Airport</strong>&nbsp;- Take I-91 South to I-84 West. Take Exit 33 onto Route 72 West toward Bristol. At end of expressway turn left onto Route 229/Middle Street. Go about 1 mile and the hotel is on the right.</p>\n\n<h3>Hotel in Bristol, Connecticut</h3>\n\n<p>Located in a charming city, midway between New York City and Boston, The DoubleTree by Hilton Hotel Bristol boasts an ideal address for business and leisure travelers. Our convenient hotel is one mile from ESPN Headquarters at the ESPN Plaza and just minutes from trendy shopping, dining and entertainment. Our hotel also offers easy access to local businesses and corporations, downtown Hartford and Bradley International Airport.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Exciting Family Adventures</strong> - The DoubleTree by Hilton Hotel Bristol is close to many exciting activities, historic landmarks and attractions. Enjoy a family day trip to Lake Compounce Amusement Park and tour the New England Carousel Museum and Imagine Nation Children&#39;s Museum. Experience the beautiful vineyards and towns along the Connecticut Wine Trail or play on the majestic slopes of the Mt. Southington Ski Area. For outdoor action, explore the Barnes Nature Center and Adventure Balloon Rides.</p>\n\n<h3>Bristol Area Attractions</h3>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Lake Compounce&nbsp;- 1 mile</li>\n	<li>Carousel Museum of New England - 1 mile</li>\n	<li>ESPN Headquarters&nbsp;- 1 mile</li>\n	<li>American Clock and Watch Museum&nbsp;- 1 mile</li>\n	<li>Connecticut Wine Trail&nbsp;- 12.8 miles</li>\n	<li>The Barnes Nature Center&nbsp;- 3 miles</li>\n	<li>Imagine Nation Museum&nbsp;- 3 miles</li>\n	<li>Giamatti Little League Center&nbsp;- 3.5 miles</li>\n	<li>Thomaston Opera House - 7.3 miles</li>\n	<li>Mt. Southington Ski Area&nbsp;- 9.2 miles</li>\n	<li>Repertory Theater of New Britain&nbsp;- 9.3 miles</li>\n	<li>Adventure Balloon Rides&nbsp;- 9.5 miles</li>\n	<li>New Britain Museum of American Art&nbsp;- 10 miles</li>\n	<li>Litchfield Hills&nbsp;- 16.3 miles</li>\n	<li>Warner Theater Torrington&nbsp;- 18 miles</li>\n	<li>CT Science Center&nbsp;- 19 miles</li>\n	<li>Connecticut Convention Center&nbsp;- 20 miles</li>\n	<li>Downtown Hartford&nbsp;- 20 miles</li>\n	<li>Lyman Orchards&nbsp;- 23 miles</li>\n	<li>Lyman Orchards Golf Course&nbsp;- 23 miles</li>\n	<li>Mohegan Sun Casino&nbsp;- 55 miles</li>\n	<li>Foxwoods Casino&nbsp;- 60 miles</li>\n	<li>Bradley International Airport - 35 miles</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\n','2016-02-24 16:33:54','2016-02-24 16:33:56',18,18,0),
	(169,3,1,205,'<h2>Things To Do in Bristol, Connecticut</h2>\n\n<p>Named one of Money magazine&#39;s &quot;best places to live&quot; in America, Bristol is a beautiful suburb of Hartford with a rich history and classic New England charm. Home to ESPN headquarters, the city offers trendy shopping and dining, entertainment, beautiful parks and many fun things to do &ndash; from the New England Carousel Museum to exploring the forest trails at the Barnes Memorial Nature Center. The city also offers a myriad of exciting events and attractions, including Lake Compounce, the oldest continuously-operated amusement park in America, Imagine Nation Children&#39;s Museum, American Clock &amp; Watch Museum and the Bristol Mum Festival. The DoubleTree by Hilton Bristol is the perfect place for a family getaway or adventure.</p>\n\n<h3>Lake Compounce Family Theme Park</h3>\n\n<p>Dive into adventure at New England&#39;s exciting family theme and waterpark with thrilling rides, coasters, water slides and shows. Ride Boulder Dash, the top wooden roller coaster in the world, and get wild at Crocodile Cove, Connecticut&#39;s largest waterpark.<br />\n<a href=\"http://www.lakecompounce.com/\">Visit Website</a><br />\n<br />\n186 Enterprise Drive,&nbsp;Bristol,&nbsp;Connecticut&nbsp;06010<br />\n860-583-3300</p>\n\n<h3>New Britain Museum of American Art</h3>\n\n<p>Founded in 1903, the New Britain Museum of American Art is the first museum in the country dedicated to American art. Experience the impressive collection of Colonial portraits, Impressionist paintings and works by artists like Georgia O&#39;Keefe and Norman Rockwell.<br />\n<a href=\"http://www.nbmaa.org/\">Visit Website</a></p>\n\n<p>56 Lexington St,&nbsp;New Britain,&nbsp;Connecticut&nbsp;06052<br />\n860-229-0257</p>\n\n<h3>American Clock and Watch Museum</h3>\n\n<p>Located in the historic heart of American clockmaking, the American Clock &amp; Watch Museum highlights the rich history, science and art of timekeeping. The world&#39;s preeminent horological museum features American clocks mostly of the 19th and early 20th century.<br />\n<a href=\"http://www.clockandwatchmuseum.org/\">Visit Website</a></p>\n\n<p>100 Maple St,&nbsp;Bristol,&nbsp;Connecticut&nbsp;06010<br />\n860-583-6070</p>\n\n<h3>Tunxis Plantation Golf Course</h3>\n\n<p>Tunxis Plantation Golf Course features 45 holes of spectacular golf in the scenic landscape of Farmington Valley. Play the links, 18-hole Green Course, picturesque White Course and the original 9-hole Red Course with views of the Farmington River.<br />\n<a href=\"http://www.tunxisgolf.com/\">Visit Website</a></p>\n\n<p>87 Town Farm Road,&nbsp;Farmington,&nbsp;Connecticut&nbsp;06032<br />\n860-677-1367</p>\n\n<h3>Connecticut Wine Trail</h3>\n\n<p>Meander through the CT Wine Trail, one of the most exciting wine regions in the country, with 24 charming wineries and stunning New England scenery. Follow the blue trail signs and sip amazing wines at wineries such as Sunset Meadow Vineyards and Miranda Vineyard.<br />\n<a href=\"http://www.ctwine.com/\">Visit Website</a></p>\n\n<p>195 Farmington Avenue,&nbsp;Farmington,&nbsp;Connecticut&nbsp;06032<br />\n860-677-5467</p>\n\n<h3>Connecticut Science Center</h3>\n\n<p>Overlooking the Connecticut River in Hartford, this attraction features interactive exhibits of science, art, nature and music in its multi-media galleries. Explore the galaxy and a black hole, learn about Connecticut&#39;s river ecosystem and experience the feeling of sound.<br />\n<a href=\"http://www.ctsciencecenter.org/\">Visit Website</a></p>\n\n<p>250 Columbus Blvd,&nbsp;Hartford,&nbsp;Connecticut&nbsp;06103<br />\n860-724-3623</p>\n\n<h3>Foxwoods Resort Casino</h3>\n\n<p>This casino is the most exciting gaming and entertainment destination in the Northeast. Foxwoods features six casinos, trendy dining, exclusive shopping, luxury spas, championship golf courses, live entertainment and outstanding concerts and shows.<br />\n<a href=\"http://www.foxwoods.com/\">Visit Website</a></p>\n\n<p>350 Trolley Line Blvd,&nbsp;Mashantucket,&nbsp;Connecticut&nbsp;06338<br />\n860-312-3000</p>\n\n<h3>Mohegan Sun Casino</h3>\n\n<p>One of the most amazing casino resorts in the country, Mohegan Sun boasts three world-class casinos, live entertainment, fine dining, shopping, a luxury spa, spectacular golf and the hottest concerts and sporting events, including the WNBA&#39;s Connecticut Sun.<br />\n<a href=\"http://www.mohegansun.com/\">Visit Website</a></p>\n\n<p>1 Mohegan Sun Blvd,&nbsp;Montville,&nbsp;Connecticut&nbsp;06382<br />\n888-226-7711</p>\n\n<h3>Rogers Orchards</h3>\n\n<p>A bicentennial farm and Connecticut landmark of eight generations of family fruit growing, Rogers Orchards sells seasonal fruits and vegetables, including vine-ripe tomatoes and sweet corn. Stock up on apples, cider and pies as you discover the local farming heritage.<br />\n<a href=\"http://www.rogersorchards.com/\">Visit Website</a></p>\n\n<p>336 Long Bottom Rd,&nbsp;Southington,&nbsp;Connecticut&nbsp;06489<br />\n860-229-4240</p>\n','2016-02-24 16:41:24','2016-02-24 16:47:22',18,18,0),
