	(223,3,1,206,'<h2>Bristol Hotel Reviews - Experience the Difference</h2>\n\n<p>With our distinctive, new look and contemporary design, the newly-remodeled DoubleTree by Hilton Bristol delivers passionate service and modern lifestyle amenities to vacation and business travelers from around the country. Discover our quintessential character, caring culture and unsurpassed hospitality by reading our latest hotel reviews. Imagine your next getaway to our upscale hotel in Bristol, Connecticut, where you feel at home and happiness is more than a warm chocolate chip cookie.</p>\n\n<div id=\"TA_selfserveprop950\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.tripadvisor.com/\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"TripAdvisor\" src=\"http://www.tripadvisor.com/img/cdsi/img2/branding/150_logo-11900-2.png\" /></a></p>\n</div>\n<script src=\"http://www.jscache.com/wejs?wtype=selfserveprop&uniq=950&locationId=487316&lang=en_US&rating=true&nreviews=4&writereviewlink=true&popIdx=true&iswide=true&border=false&display_version=2\"></script>\n\n<p>&quot;Unbelievable Service, Outstanding Hotel!&quot;<br />\n<br />\nAfter being on the road for a week and staying in five different hotels, I arrived to this wonderful place and have been amazed since I checked in! Staff is beyond wonderful, room is immaculate, hotel grounds are beautiful and I can honestly say, this is the nicest place I have stayed in with a $100-300 price range. This hotel is so overwhelmingly wonderful, I had to write a review immediately &ndash; less than an hour after I checked in! 15 minutes or so after arriving at my room, the front desk called to make sure the room was acceptable and ask if there is anything I need. Now THAT hasn&#39;t happened at any other hotel I have stayed at in a long time. The staff here go out of their way to treat guests like royalty! So happy I decided to stay here! Thanks, Doubletree &ndash; I haven&#39;t even left yet but I will guarantee I&#39;ll be back!! Stayed May 2015, traveled on business<br />\n<br />\n&quot;Clean &amp; Modern Doubletree in Bristol&quot;<br />\n<br />\nOur family of five had a great stay in the Doubletree hotel in Bristol, CT. We had an early event nearby which prompted our choice to stay there. The queen suite was so comfortable and spacious, we wish all hotels we stay in had this arrangement. The kids had a great time in the pool. The staff were very friendly and service was wonderful. We highly recommend this hotel. &ndash; by Susan B. (New Canaan, CT) on 3/31/14. Stay date: Mar 2014<br />\n<br />\n&quot;ESPN&quot;<br />\n<br />\nNear the corporate headquarters of ESPN, this hotel was conveniently located. The staff was very helpful and friendly. Can&#39;t beat the warm cookie at check-in! Room was spacious and the workout area was&nbsp;very nice. Enjoyable breakfast. &ndash; by Jill B. (Buffalo, NY) on 3/31/14. Stay date: Mar 2014<br />\n<br />\n&quot;A Must Stay!&quot;<br />\n<br />\nFrom the time we walked in the front door, we were impressed. From the friendly greeting (with a delicious warm chocolate chip cookie, and if you have ever had one of these you know what I am talking about) to the spacious room, my experience at the hotel far exceeded my expectations. The sports bar was right on the money. There were several TVs&nbsp;with many games to choose from. The food was good and reasonably priced. The service was also very good. This place has a fitness center and a heated pool, although we did not get to experience either due to time restrictions on my part. The room was very nice and modern with two queen beds and HDTV. It also has a Keurig coffee maker which was great for that immediate morning cup. I highly recommend this hotel and it will be my choice the next time I&#39;m staying in Bristol. &ndash; by Mike P. (North Providence, RI) on 3/30/14. Stay date: Mar 2014<br />\n<br />\n&quot;Repeatedly Blown Away at the Customer Service.&quot;<br />\n<br />\nJust a brief note to tell you about my experience and the attitudes at the Bristol Doubletree Hotel. I am diamond at Hilton and Gold at Marriott, so needless to say I travel frequently. I am just finishing up my third stay here and I am repeatedly blown away at the customer service. Here are a few examples.<br />\n<br />\nEvelyis - a breathe of sunshine. She has an attitude of &quot;what else can I do, I love helping you.&quot; She gets it before I know I want it.<br />\n<br />\nRestaurant - The first time I was here they had a duck special. The second time I was here I asked if it was one of the specials. It wasn&#39;t but they made if for me anyway. It was delicious.<br />\n<br />\nLast time I was here I had left my blazer in the room. When I arrived yesterday my blazer was dry cleaned, pressed and waiting for me in my room. Now, this is a wow! I asked who was in charge of doing this. It was Miguel.<br />\n<br />\nI have never been to a hotel where EVERYONE goes above and beyond. This attitude and work ethic obviously comes from the top. Kudos, you are doing an amazing job.<br />\n<br />\nSincerely,<br />\nAnonymous</p>\n','2016-02-26 11:11:41','2016-02-26 11:11:41',15,15,0),
